sentences: Nana Azuki (AZUKI七, Azuki Nana) (born July 26, 1974) is a Japanese musical lyricist and keyboardist under Giza Studio label.
After graduating from college in 1999, she began showing off her talents in a number of auditions.

After creating the band Garnet Crow in 1999 as a indie band and in 2000 as a major band, she has been continuing providing work to a number of Giza Studio artists as Takaoka Ai, Shiori Takei, Hayami Kishimoto and Sayuri Iwata.

After Garnet Crow disbanded, she composed one song for the Japanese singer Meg in 2014.
As of 2018, her whereabouts are unknown.
